docs.text: will hunting ( matt damon ) is a natural genius .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: for a movie character , that's usually a death sentence .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it's a trait associated with what my brother calls " too good for this world " movies , like phenomenon or powder .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: forgive me for spoiling the ending , but will doesn't die .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this is no formula movie .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in fact , it's quite fresh and original .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it's a character study more than anything , and that's not surprising , considering it was written by two actors : damon and co-star ben affleck .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: will works whatever kind of job he can get .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: first he's a janitor , then he works construction .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: off-screen he speed reads books on any academic subject that interests him .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: on-screen he hangs out with his friends , picking fights in robust , romanticized-hemingway fashion .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: lambeau ( stellan skarsgard from breaking the waves ) , a math professor , learns that the janitor ( will ) is a genius with a special talent for advanced mathematics .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: having confirmed he's not a fluke or a savant , he does what he can to get will into the education system .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he is firmly rejected .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: finally , will lands in jail for one of his fights .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: lambeau can get him probation instead of prison time as long as will agrees to therapy sessions and to discussing mathematics with him .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: will ( barely ) decides to go for the therapy over prison .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: lambeau treats will like a son .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he's proud of , and amazed by , will's accomplishments in mathematics .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he encourages will and tries to give him structure , knowing that , with a little discipline , he could be bigger than einstein .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: will isn't really interested in academia .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he knows he would be the best in his field , and therefore spend all of his time in an office , explaining math to people like lambeau .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he would rather work construction , which breaks lambeau's heart .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: meanwhile , will attends his mandated therapy sessions .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it's not long before he shreds all the therapists on lambeau's " a " list .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: will has read enough psychology to know the tricks of the trade , and how to keep them from affecting him .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: shrink after shrink refuses to return after will's mockery .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: lambeau's last hope is his old college roommate , now a psychology teacher at a small-time community college .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: knowing that will is going to try to shred him too , sean ( robin williams ) agrees to take him on as a favor to lambeau and for the chance to meet this next einstein .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: true to form , will finds sean's emotional weakness and attacks .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but unlike the other shrinks , sean knows what he is in for and continues the sessions .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: like a foster mother with a fussy child , sean knows that the attacks are defensive and is able to take them in stride .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: like the foster mother , sean knows that time and quiet patience is the only approach .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: robin williams is excellent in this role .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he's not an actor with a great range , but in the right roles he has great depth .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in this movie , as in awakenings , there comes a point when the quiet , shy man accomplishes something of great personal importance , and a smile of pure joy spreads up to his eyes .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: williams is the only actor i can name who can make an audience cry just by smiling .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: i have compared will to a foster child and that's not entirely fair .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: emotionally , he has a lot to learn , but he is not a child .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he has thought about his life and made rational decisions about what he wants .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: sean , his girlfriend , his pals , and lambeau all help him grow , but he didn't start out asking for , or particularly needing , help .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: his exceptional gift singled him out , and those who love him kept pushing him in the right direction .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: if i had to say anything bad about good will hunting is that it walks the line between drama and melodrama .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it's too sentimental and uplifiting for a straight drama , but the emotions are too subtle for melodrama .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it is emotionally engaging , but it's not quite larger than life .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this isn't a problem per se , but at times i didn't know quite how to take it .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but this is a relatively small complaint about a very good movie .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: a good movie allows its characters to learn and grow .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it doesn't just happen ; it takes a good script , good acting , and good direction .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: good will hunting has all three .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: if you are at all inclined to see it , by all means , go .
docs.label: positive
